# DOQS workflow

## Before closing a design task

- [ ] SysML / params / BOM updated as needed (requirements only in SysML).
- [ ] `python doqs/scripts/validate_okh.py`
- [ ] `python doqs/scripts/validate_build.py` if lockfiles changed
- [ ] `python doqs/scripts/build_graph.py` if `hasComponent` or builds changed
- [ ] `python doqs/scripts/check_links.py`
- [ ] Submodule `doqs/` present and up to date (`git submodule update --init`)
- [ ] Conventional commit message (`cad`, `arch`, `okh`, `params`, `interface`, `build`, …)

## Modules

- Every module folder has: `bom/`, `cad/`, `architecture/`, `docs/`, `manufacturing/`, `modules/`.
- Adapters under `modules/adapters/` for interface version bridges.
- Submodule workflow: commit inside `modules/<name>/`, then bump pointer in parent repo.

## Interfaces

Breaking port changes bump interface **major** version in SysML name and OKH `version`. Plan adapter modules when needed.

## Builds

Physical machines: `builds/<id>/build.toml` pins each module version and parametric `model`. Record changes in `[[modification]]`.
